    Academic Partners

    HOW DO WE PARTNER

    ALC Bridge assists both language professionals and students in locating, investigating, and securing career-oriented employment opportunities within the language services sector. To become an Educational Partner with ALC Bridge, email bridge@alcus.org to learn more and book a presentation.

    OUR ACADEMIC PARTNERS

    Michigan State University

    Regarded as one of the best research universities worldwide, Michigan State University is the leading land-grant institution in the country. Along with giving a diverse and inclusive academic community opportunities that can change lives, Spartans tackle the world's most pressing problems daily.

    Alverno College

    Our pioneering abilities-based approach to education has been studied by others around the globe. We are trailblazers. Nearly 70 percent of our incoming students are the first in their families to attend college. We are Wisconsin's first Hispanic-Serving Institution.

    Cornell University

    Cornell University is renowned for its research in cancer biology, genomics, and regenerative medicine, which has been critical to developing new treatments for disease. The undergraduate programs at Cornell are offered across eight colleges and schools: College of Agriculture and Life Sciences.

    Old Dominion University

    Old Dominion University, located in Norfolk, is Virginia's forward-focused public doctoral research university with more than 24,000 students, rigorous academics, an energetic residential community and initiatives that contribute $2.6 billion annually to Virginia's economy.

    University of Houston Downtown

    Founded in 1974, UHD is the second largest, four-year university in Houston and is recognized nationally as a Hispanic-Serving Institution, Minority-Serving Institution and Military-Friendly School.

    Brigham Young University

    Known for its excellence in language education, BYU regularly offers courses in 62 different languages. About 65% of students speak a second language. In addition to its main location in Provo, BYU has campuses in Idaho and Hawaii.

    Carnegie Mellon University

    Carnegie Mellon is known for its advances in research and new fields of study, home to many firsts in computer science (including the first machine learning, robotics, and computational biology departments), pioneering the field of management science, and the first drama program in the USA.

    Kent State University

    Kent State University is known for its outstanding academics, but we also encourage all students to get involved on campus. There are more than 370 clubs and organizations on campus, some specifically for international students. There are also 18 sports teams and 32 sororities and fraternities.

    Middlebury Institute of International Studies at Monterey

    The Middlebury Institute of International Studies is a graduate school of Middlebury College and training ground for developing and implementing practical solutions. It is home to some of the world's leading experts in global security, sustainability, development, education, and language services.

    Metropolitan State University of Denver

    Metropolitan State University of Denver was founded in 1965 as an opportunity school. By design, MSU Denver is required to be accessible to all, which is why it consistently has some of the lowest tuitions of four-year Colorado colleges and universities. Nearly 54% of the student body are students of color.

    Montclair State

    Montclair was named one of America's Best Bang for the Buck Colleges by Washington Monthly's 2023 College Guide. The magazine also recognized the University as a Voter Friendly Campus and one of the Best Colleges for Student Voting.

    Rutgers University Newark

    Rutgers UniversityNewark is one of three regional campuses of Rutgers University, a public land-grant research university consisting of four campuses in New Jersey.

    New York University

    The largest private research university in the US, NYU provides a rigorous, demanding education to more than 65,000 students and undertakes $1.27 billion in research annually.

    Salem State University

    Salem State is a public university located in Salem, Massachusetts in the Boston Area. It is a small institution with an enrollment of 3,924 undergraduate students. The Salem State acceptance rate is 93%. Popular majors include Nursing, Psychology, and Criminal Justice and Law Enforcement Administration.

    Utah Valley University

    Utah Valley University is the largest public university in the state of Utah, and one of a few in the nation offering a dual-mission model that combines the rigor and richness of a first-rate teaching university with the openness and vocational programs of a community college.

    Tarleton State University

    Tarleton State is considered a First Scholar Designation with over 51% of students first-generation. Third largest agricultural program among non-land grant universities in the nation.

    University of Florida

    One of America's all-around best universities, the University of Florida drives future-making education, eye-opening discoveries, life-saving health care, and community-building collaboration for our state, our nation, and our world.

    University of Michigan

    The University of Michigan is known for its excellence in academics, research, and athletics. It is one of the top public universities in the United States and has consistently ranked among the best universities in the world.Oct 24, 2022

    The University of New Mexico

    We are recognized as a Carnegie Highest Research Activity Institution and a federally designated Hispanic Serving Institution.

    University of Washington

    Founded in 1861, the University of Washington is one of the world's most prestigious universities. The UW enrolls more than 60,000 students each year and thrives as a center for groundbreaking research in a variety of fields, including medicine, education, public affairs, aeronautics and business.

    University of Virginia

    The University is an iconic public institution of higher education, boasting nationally ranked schools and programs, diverse and distinguished faculty, a major academic medical center and proud history as a renowned research university.

    Weber State University

    Weber State is an above-average public university located in Ogden, Utah in the Salt Lake City Area. It is a large institution with an enrollment of 11,548 undergraduate students. The Weber State acceptance rate is 100%. Popular majors include Liberal Arts and Humanities, Nursing, and Computer Science.

    University of Wisconsin-Madison

    UW-Madison is home to a number of important scientific firsts including our work in the area of stem cells, bone marrow transplants, wildlife management, and more.

    University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee

    We are nationally recognized for our undergraduate research, and UWM students get real-world experiences that shape their education and careers, such as paid internships, entrepreneurship programs and community-based classes and volunteer opportunities.
